## Final Quality Checklist

Before finalizing, verify:

- The repository was treated as authoritative evidence of implemented reality.
- Implementation was not confused with capability realization.
- Every epic acceptance criterion was evaluated.
- Every milestone was evaluated individually.
- Every milestone acceptance criterion was evaluated.
- Epic success conditions were evaluated separately from acceptance criteria.
- Projection invariants were checked.
- Epic constraints were checked.
- Milestone dependencies were checked.
- Drift was evaluated independently from completion.
- Positive drift was considered.
- Negative drift was considered.
- Validation gaps were identified.
- Residual work was identified.
- Closure recommendation follows from evidence.
- No roadmap update was performed.
- No roadmap completion context update was performed.
- No epic or milestone spec was modified.
- No implementation tasks were created.
- Repository observations were compressed into certification and strategic findings.
- Canonical projection vocabulary was preserved.